statement.p:
Let L be a line through the origin in \R^2. The reflection over L is the linear transformation ref_L: \R^2 \to \R^2 defined by
                ref_L(x) = x-2x_{L^\perp} = 2proj_L(x) - x.


Find the points corresponding to ref_L(u), ref_L(v), and ref_L(w) in the picture below. [Hint: Think geometrically]

                            \begin{tikzpicture}
                             \draw[help lines, black!30] (-2,-2) grid (2,2);
                             \useasboundingbox (-2,-2) rectangle (2,2);
                             \draw[->] (-2,0) -- (2,0);
                             \draw[->] (0,-2) -- (0,2);
                             \draw[thick] (-2,2) -- node[pos=.4,above] {$L$} (2,-2);
                             \point["$u$"] (u) at (-.5,1.5);
                             \point["$v$"] (v) at (-1,-1);
                             \point["$w$" anchor=200] (w) at (1,-1);
                            \end{tikzpicture}
